external_knowledge:
- "voyagers" refers to the users who access the films;
- "films from the second decade of the millennium" refers to films released since 2010;
- "missed by the majority or gently acknowledged" refers to films either not rated or rated with a maximum of 7;
- "frequent enough to cast a shadow over the less-traveled paths" means the films have been accessed more than five times;
- "alphabetically by user names" means the results are sorted by the users' names;
- "limited to the first 10 entries" means the result list is capped at 10 entries.

sql:
SELECT title 
FROM films 
WHERE film_id NOT IN (SELECT film_id FROM access_logs);

external_knowledge:
- 'DVD in 1080p resolution' refers to a specific format of digital video disc with a high-definition resolution;
- 'New millennium (2010)' refers to the time period starting from the year 2010;
- 'Shimmering average ratings' are the reflective scores given to each film, categorized as 'Excellent' if the score is 8 or above, 'Good' if it is between 6 and 7.99, and 'Average or Below' for anything below 6.

sql:
SELECT country, COUNT(DISTINCT film_id) AS NumberOfFilms
FROM films
GROUP BY country;

external_knowledge:
- 'major projects' refers to films directed; 
- 'key figures' in this context means directors;
- 'helmsman' is a metaphorical term for a director in film-making.

sql:
SELECT title, original_title, year, country
FROM films
WHERE rating = (SELECT MIN(rating) FROM films);

external_knowledge:
- "shone the brightest" metaphorically refers to users who have written the most reviews; 
- "constellation of review writers" refers to the group of users who have written reviews;
- "illuminated the night sky" metaphorically refers to the act of writing reviews.

- 'accolades' are synonymous with 'awards' in this context;
- 'most recognized films' refer to those with a higher number of awards;
- 'less celebrated' implies fewer awards received.

sql:
SELECT films.title, films.rating
FROM films
JOIN access_logs ON films.film_id = access_logs.film_id;
